<DOC><DOCNO> WSJ880408-0136 </DOCNO><HL> Wheelabrator Technologies </HL><SO> </SO><CO> WHTI KLT </CO><DATELINE> HAMPTON, N.H.  </DATELINE><TEXT>   Wheelabrator Technologies Inc. said that it and Kansas City Power andamp; Light Co. will build and own an $80 million waste-to-energy plant in the Kansas City, Mo., area.    The facility, scheduled for operation in 1993, will turn 800 tons of refuse a day into enough electricity to serve 15,000 families. The plan is subject to obtaining environmental permits. Wheelabrator builds and runs waste-to-energy plants. </TEXT></DOC>